OL,3,CWales' pothole crisis dubbed 'the
OL,4,Cworst nightmare ever' for drivers
OL,6,FMatthew Callaghan, from Newport,
OL,7,Fdamaged his car while driving over a
OL,8,Fpothole in the city.
OL,10,FIn 2025, he measured the pothole to be
OL,11,Fsix inches deep. He said: "The wheels
OL,12,F(of the car) were pointing in the
OL,13,Fwrong direction.
OL,15,F"The act of trying to get out of the
OL,16,Fpothole snapped the track rod and bent
OL,17,Fthe strut, causing damage to other
OL,18,Fsuspension parts. The car was in the
OL,19,Fgarage for the best part of a week."
OL,26,@tD@ApmtD@Lpn
